Home Work 4:
Exercise - I:
1. Please write sample programs to demonstrate the below OOP concepts:
a. Polymorphism (method overloading and method overriding)
b. Abstraction (interface and Abstract Class)
(Please check the practiced programs in the attached project)

Exercise - II:
1. Create a Bank interface and declare banking operation methods and variables
2. Create classes BarclaysBank , LloydsBank or TescoBank.....
and implement the Bank interface methods in all the above classes
implement the method differently in different classes
3. Create TestBank class and access the methods of above classes

Exercise - III:
1. Demonstrate using switch statements with number, character and string expression

Exercise - IV: 
1. Write a program to get the character at the given index within the String
2. Write a program to concatenate a given string to the end of another string
3. Write a program to test if a given string contains the specified string
4. Write a program to check whether a given string ends with the contents of another string.
5. Write a program to compare a given string to another string, ignoring case considerations.
6. Write a program to get the length of a given string.
7. Write a program to replace all the 'd' characters with 'f' characters
8. Write a program to get a substring of a given string between two specified positions.
9. Write a program to convert all the characters in a string to lowercase

Exercise - V:
1. Create a class with a method which can generate random number and random email address, and random username

Exercise - VI:
1.Create a class with calculation methods using Math class methods.
